Package: diseq
Title: Estimation Methods for Markets in Disequilibrium
Version: 0.0.4.9011
Authors@R: person(
        "Pantelis", "Karapanagiotis", email = "pikappa.devel@gmail.com", 
        role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9871-1908")
    )
Description: The diseq package provides a toolkit of methods that can be used to 
    estimate markets in equilibrium and disequilibrium. Specifically, it allows the
    estimation of an equilibrium and four disequilibrium model specifications. It
    also provides post-estimation analysis tools, such as aggregation and marginal
    effects calculations. The estimation methods are based on full information
    maximum likelihood techniques. The equilibrium estimation constitutes a special
    case of a system of simultaneous equations. The disequilibrium estimation is
    based on Maddala and Nelson (1974) <doi:10.2307/1914215>. The package takes
    advantage of the expressions of the gradients of the likelihoods given in
    Karapanagiotis (2020).
